verses.text_plain: O God, why hast thou cast us off for ever? why doth thine anger smoke against the sheep of thy pasture?
verses.verse_html:
1O God, why hast thou cast us off for ever? why doth thine anger smoke against the sheep of thy pasture? ▼
▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Asaph to give instruction

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Asaph to give instruction
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Asaph to give instruction

verses.text_plain: Remember thy congregation, which thou hast purchased of old; the rod of thine inheritance, which thou hast redeemed; this mount Zion, wherein thou hast dwelt.
verses.verse_html:
2Remember thy congregation, which thou hast purchased of old; the rod of thine inheritance, which thou hast redeemed; this mount Zion, wherein thou hast dwelt. ▼
▼ rod: or, tribe

verses.text_plain: Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations; even all that the enemy hath done wickedly in the sanctuary.
verses.verse_html: 3Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations; even all that the enemy hath done wickedly in the sanctuary.

verses.text_plain: Thine enemies roar in the midst of thy congregations; they set up their ensigns for signs.
verses.verse_html: 4Thine enemies roar in the midst of thy congregations; they set up their ensigns for signs.

verses.text_plain: A man was famous according as he had lifted up axes upon the thick trees.
verses.verse_html: 5A man was famous according as he had lifted up axes upon the thick trees.

tokens.text: according as he had lifted up

verses.text_plain: But now they break down the carved work thereof at once with axes and hammers.
verses.verse_html: 6But now they break down the carved work thereof at once with axes and hammers.

verses.text_plain: They have cast fire into thy sanctuary, they have defiled by casting down the dwelling place of thy name to the ground.
verses.verse_html:
7They have cast fire into thy sanctuary, they have defiled by casting down the dwelling place of thy name to the ground. ▼
▼ They have cast…: Heb. They have sent thy sanctuary unto the fire

footnotes.body_text: ▼ They have cast…: Heb. They have sent thy sanctuary unto the fire
footnotes.body_html: ▼ They have cast…: Heb. They have sent thy sanctuary unto the fire

verses.text_plain: They said in their hearts, Let us destroy them together: they have burned up all the synagogues of God in the land.
verses.verse_html:
8They said in their hearts, Let us destroy them together: they have burned up all the synagogues of God in the land. ▼
▼ destroy: Heb. break

verses.text_plain: We see not our signs: there is no more any prophet: neither is there among us any that knoweth how long.
verses.verse_html: 9We see not our signs: there is no more any prophet: neither is there among us any that knoweth how long.

verses.text_plain: O God, how long shall the adversary reproach? shall the enemy blaspheme thy name for ever?
verses.verse_html: 10O God, how long shall the adversary reproach? shall the enemy blaspheme thy name for ever?

verses.text_plain: Why withdrawest thou thy hand, even thy right hand? pluck it out of thy bosom.
verses.verse_html: 11Why withdrawest thou thy hand, even thy right hand? pluck it out of thy bosom.

verses.text_plain: For God is my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 12For God is my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.

verses.text_plain: Thou didst divide the sea by thy strength: thou brakest the heads of the dragons in the waters.
verses.verse_html:
13Thou didst divide the sea by thy strength: thou brakest the heads of the dragons in the waters. ▼
▼ divide: Heb. break
 , ▼
▼ dragons: or, whales

verses.text_plain: Thou brakest the heads of leviathan in pieces, and gavest him to be meat to the people inhabiting the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 14Thou brakest the heads of leviathan in pieces, and gavest him to be meat to the people inhabiting the wilderness.

verses.text_plain: Thou didst cleave the fountain and the flood: thou driedst up mighty rivers.
verses.verse_html:
15Thou didst cleave the fountain and the flood: thou driedst up mighty rivers. ▼
▼ mighty…: Heb. rivers of strength

footnotes.body_html: ▼ mighty…: Heb. rivers of strength

verses.text_plain: The day is thine, the night also is thine: thou hast prepared the light and the sun.
verses.verse_html: 16The day is thine, the night also is thine: thou hast prepared the light and the sun.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast set all the borders of the earth: thou hast made summer and winter.
verses.verse_html:
17Thou hast set all the borders of the earth: thou hast made summer and winter. ▼
▼ made: Heb. made them

footnotes.body_html: ▼ made: Heb. made them

verses.text_plain: Remember this, that the enemy hath reproached, O Lord, and that the foolish people have blasphemed thy name.
verses.verse_html: 18Remember this, that the enemy hath reproached, O Lord, and that the foolish people have blasphemed thy name.

verses.text_plain: O deliver not the soul of thy turtledove unto the multitude of the wicked: forget not the congregation of thy poor for ever.
verses.verse_html: 19O deliver not the soul of thy turtledove unto the multitude of the wicked: forget not the congregation of thy poor for ever.

verses.text_plain: Have respect unto the covenant: for the dark places of the earth are full of the habitations of cruelty.
verses.verse_html: 20Have respect unto the covenant: for the dark places of the earth are full of the habitations of cruelty.

verses.text_plain: O let not the oppressed return ashamed: let the poor and needy praise thy name.
verses.verse_html: 21O let not the oppressed return ashamed: let the poor and needy praise thy name.

verses.text_plain: Arise, O God, plead thine own cause: remember how the foolish man reproacheth thee daily.
verses.verse_html: 22Arise, O God, plead thine own cause: remember how the foolish man reproacheth thee daily.

verses.text_plain: Forget not the voice of thine enemies: the tumult of those that rise up against thee increaseth continually.
verses.verse_html:
23Forget not the voice of thine enemies: the tumult of those that rise up against thee increaseth continually. ▼
▼ increaseth: Heb. ascendeth
